project.name: Thingspeak
project.notes: Lookup sensor data from IoT devices around the globe. Click on Alonzo to search for sensor in the current location by tags.

block.l: function deg2rad(deg) { return deg * (Math.PI/180) } var R = 6371; // Radius of the earth in km var dLat = deg2rad(lat2-lat1); // deg2rad below var dLon = deg2rad(lon2-lon1); var a = Math.sin(dLat/2) * Math.sin(dLat/2) + Math.cos(deg2rad(lat1)) * Math.cos(deg2rad(lat2)) * Math.sin(dLon/2) * Math.sin(dLon/2) ; var c = 2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(a), Math.sqrt(1-a)); var d = R * c; // Distance in km return d;

scripts.comment: report stops the loop as soon as value that we are looking for is found

item.l: Located at Institute for Software Integrated Systems (Vanderbilt University)
place to store Aquarium regulator data. (hopefully)
Gathers weather data from a station in St. Louis.
Elements of a sensor network based on the same open-source hardware that powers the unmanned aerial systems of dronejournalism.org.
Temperature inside Shop in the backyard. Temperature is taken from a TMP175 I2C temperature sensor connected to an Arduino UNO.
dht22 temperature humidity sensor, esp8266 wifi,
ds18b20 temp probe updating via LoRa Gateway obtained from http://cpham.perso.univ-pau.fr/LORA/RPIgateway.html
Garage temperature and relative humidity near the water pipes
Air & Water temperatures from the sunny shores of Lake Norman NC
Arduino Uno R3 w/ Ethernet shield and AD22100ktz Temp sensor recording temperature in my office. In the future will include Humidity sensor.
The is BME 280 is attached to my photon. It is setup to measure temperature, humidity and barometric pressure.

Data from a Photon in my garden that is used to water my plants. The watering cycle is based on the value of 3 soil moisture sensors placed throughout the garden. If the value of any drops below the watering threshold, a water pump hooked up to a 55-gallo
This channel tracks temperature and humidity from Milin's room.
tracking how indoor air correlates with outdoor air
Temperature Battery Humidity Heat Pump Bear Creek Thermostat
Air temperature in the greenhouse. Raspberry Pi and a DS18B20 temperature sensor.
Temp inside my house. New project soon
hih6030-021-001 for temp and humidity. nRF24L01, pic18f26k22.
hih6030-021-001 for temp and humidity. LPC1114 MCU.
kitchen temp, humidity, mq2 gas sensors. powered by an electric imp with a hih6030-021-001.
hih6030-021-001 for temp and humidity. KP235 for barometer. PIC18F26K80 MCU (12-bit ADC)
hih6030-021-001 for temp and humidity. MSP430G2553 MCU
This channel provides weather information using one BMP180 and two DHT22 sensors(inside, outside) that communicate with a Nodemcu(esp8266).
Light and temperature readings from my chicken coop. You can see the coop at www.thechickinn.us

ESP8266 Wifi module Temp logger on ThingSpeak Using DS18B20 Temperature Sensors. Just experimenting with IoT... And if you are looking at the data and wondering... No, I do not have Air Conditioning. :(
Monitor wood stove water temp and basement with 1 wire sensors

Uses a D1 Mini and Arduino code with an HTU21D for ambient sensing and two DS18B20 OneWire sensors for inlet and outlet temperature measurement. If the inlet and outlet temps diverge by more than 3C this indicates the unit is heating or cooling. A relay
This thing sends the current temperature and Humidity from a DHT22 sensor via my ESP8266 ESP201 module!!! By: Thomas Rosario.
This weather station was designed by Karl Berger. This weather station was built by Turner Bumbary and he hopes to use the weather data to forecast weather in developing countries.
This is the weather station kit by W4KRL. As of 12 November 2016, it is monitoring the outside weather.
Located at Institute for Software Integrated Systems (Vanderbilt University)
